animal.description:
Hi There! My name is Ben, it's very nice to meet you! Let me tell you a bit about myself; I am a 50lb, 7 year old, Husky who is ready to meet his Furever Family! 

I am told by my hooman friends how handsome, sweet and goofy I am... I don't really know what that means but the hoomans smile, then give me kisses and pets when they say it, so when they say it I'm thinking what they are saying is  a good thing, so I give kisses right back!

Where was I? Oh yes I was telling you about ME! I like to meet other doggies but they may need a minute to warm up to my sunny disposition. I love all sizes and ages of hoomans too but I can't have those smaller and younger hoomans to be TOO small or young! As you might be able to see from my pictures, my right eye looks a bit funny. It's due to a condition that makes me blind in that eye, but what the hoomans don't know, is that it actually sees into the future.... Wait I'm getting something... I see my future furever family! Hopefully they find me soon! 

If you are interested in meeting me, please email adoption@sdsanctuary.com to schedule a visit with me!

animal.description:
Double the fun and double the love with these 2 amazing dogs! Zuma and Marshall are both looking for their forever home together. This brother and sister duo are 5yr old Pug/Terrier mixes. They both weigh approximately 24lbs and are done growing. They both get along with other dogs and have even lived with cats. They are friendly and have lived with children of all ages! Zuma is very outgoing where Marshall is a little shy at first. Once he has been given the ok by his sister, he is the biggest sweetheart. They both are housebroken, kennel trained and even know how to use a doggie door. Zuma and Marshall love to go on walks and do well on car rides. Zuma, unfortunately started experiencing seizures at home and when at the groomer. With the help of her daily meds of Levetiracetam she has been successfully enjoying life without a problem. Zuma and Marshall are spayed and neutered, are up to date on vaccines, microchipped and vet checked. Their adoption fee is $400 (for the pair) which includes a complimentary veterinary visit. To potentially adopt him, please come to our shelter location at 1102 W. Hatcher Rd. Phoenix, AZ 85021 anytime during business hours. We are open Tuesday-Sunday from 11AM-6PM. --COVID update: To adhere to CDC guidelines, we are open for adoptions only at a max capacity of 10 people in the building at a time. Masks/face coverings are required. For the safety of our staff and customers, we ask that you practice social distancing, sanitization, and if exposed to Covid-19 or sick to please stay home.--

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Raven! I’m a cattle dog / lab mix. I’m springy at 35 lbs and a fun 2 year old. I’m quiet through the night in my medium crate. I looove walks, enjoy the occasional jog, and will play fetch whenever and wherever. I hope snuggle time lasts all day long. I’m a smart gal and I’ll listen when you need me too. I’m super cute when I snooze too. My adoption fee is $250.00.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description: BELLA is another one of the mother and pup combinations Adopt Me! took in last year.   Her puppies have all been adopted and now it's time for Bella. She loves to cuddle as well as play.   She had a few initial accidents but is now very much house trained.   She weighs 47 lbs and is full grown.   If interested in adopting, our process begins with the application which can be found at www.adoptmebluegrasspetrescue.

I have been at the shelter since Jan 23, 2021. Meet Colt! This handsome and smart fella came to the shelter as a stray so shelter staff are still getting to know him. Personality: Colt can be a bit shy when meeting new people but warms up quickly with patience and treats! Once comfortable, he is extremely playful and affectionate. He knows how to sit and give paw! History: His history with other dogs is unknown, however we recommend no small pets (cats, dogs, etc). We always recommend slow and careful introductions over time to any resident pets. Energy levels: Colt has ALL the energy! He would love to run all day with you and play fetch in your backyard! Ideal home: Due to Colt`s handsome singing voice, he is not fit for homes with shared walls (apartments, condos, etc). He would GREATLY appreciate a FULLY FENCED yard, as once he warms up, he is an energetic boy! Due to his past, he cannot be left unattended outside. Family: Colt would love to go to a home with TEENS/ADULTS that have shy dog experience, as everyone needs to be able handle his size/energy. Everyone in the home should be present at time of meeting. Does he sound like the big boy for you? Come down and meet him today! **THIS DOG IS NOT AT OUR SHELTER EMAIL DOGFOSTER@THEHUMANESOCIETY.ORG**

animal.description: My Buddy, My Buddy, Wherever I go, he goes. My Buddy, My Buddy, I'll teach him everything that I know. My Buddy and me, Like to climb up a tree. My buddy and me, We're the best friends that could be. My Buddy, My Buddy, My Buddy and Me! Children of the 80s will remember that jingle (and have it stuck in their heads for the next 2-5 weeks). My Buddy was a childs toy, but with this sweet, handsome pooch, my Buddy takes on a whole new, and way better meaning! Buddy may not actually want to climb a tree with you, but he definitely wants to learn from you and be your very best friend!! In his prior home, Buddy did well with a resident Chihuahua and with kids as young as 4. He was an outdoor pet in his last home, so needs to find a forever home where hell have a place inside with his family. Buddy is a sweet, squishy, affectionate boy who loves being with his person. When meeting other dogs in PACC playgroup, Buddy was tolerant, playful and respectful of corrections from both the other dogs and the handlers in the yard. animal.description:
Hello!  I'm Blue!  I'm a 2 year chow mix who weighs about 65lbs.  I've spent most of my life living outside so I'm learning to live the good life. I really like it so far.  I go into my crate when asked and am nice and quiet in it.  I've only had one accident in the house so far, which is pretty good since I'm used to living outside.  My foster mom tells me I'm the best boy.  I love running around the yard with my foster siblings (they are big and small) & will sometimes chase the cat when he runs by me.  I'm learning to play with toys and like them so far.  I'm pretty obedient, but could use some basic manners since I'm a big boy. I'm learning to walk on a leash and am pretty strong.  If you think you are ready for a friendly fluffy friend in your life, apply today!  My adoption fee is $250.00.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
Introducing Buddy - a lovable goofball looking for his forever home.  He is a smart boy just dying to show you all of his tricks - he can sit, lay down, and even shake.    He has a medium energy level.  He equally loves taking naps next to his people, going for a walk or a run, or playing fetch.  He does well with the other big dogs in his foster home, and he would make a great family dog.  
He is a neutered, 7-month-old dutch shepherd mix that currently weighs about 45 lbs.  He is still working on his housetraining but does know what to do when he goes outside.   He is extremely treat-motivated (which makes him guilty of a little counter surfing).  That, combined with his intelligence, should make him easy to train.

Buddy was found as a stray and taken in by someone for two weeks while looking for his family. He was then surrendered to the shelter, where his microchip number was tracked further without result. Nobody came for him.

He has now found his way to our rescue and is looking for a new home. His energy level is moderate...not too bad for a puppy we were told. 

Buddy Does NOT crate well. He is great outside his crate but will dig and get  upset when confined in a crate.


If interested in adopting please fill out our no obligation online application at www.puppypawsrescue.org 

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies)  and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

Hi, my name is Sadie! I'm estimated to be a Lab mix born around 1/1/2013. I weight around 50 pounds. I was surrendered to the shelter in Texas with Paula.  They were told that we are between 8 - 10 years in age and I might be Paula's mom.  Our owner passed away and not much information was left about us.  We love to go to walks and love attention.  We have spent our whole lives together and want to continue with that so we do need to be adopted together. Apply for us today!

My adoption fee is $60.00. Adoption applications can be filled out at CCHS or online through our website, www.cchs-petshelter.org. Applications are not first come, first served. All applications will be reviewed by the adoption committee and the home chosen will be the one considered to be the best match. All dogs and puppies have been vaccinated for Distemper and Bordetella, dewormed and microchipped. If old enough, they will be vaccinated for Rabies and blood tested for Heartworm, Lymes, Anaplasmosis and Erlichiosis. Dogs and puppies will be spayed or neutered before adoption.

CCHS is proud to be a No-Kill Humane Society. As a private, non-profit charity, our work depends on donations and volunteers to keep going. We are committed to helping the animals that enter our doors and finding each the best possible forever home. CCHS has been inspected and licensed by the Department of Animal Health - DATCP. Our license is #268235-DS

animal.description:
****Please do not message the rescue asking if this dog is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Milo 
*Age: 1 year
*Current Weight: 70
*Rescued from: Texas
*Adoption fee: $375 
*Health: up to date on required vaccines

Meet Milo, this excited active boy is looking for his furever home. Unfortunately, his size and energy level quickly outgrew the apartment life of his previous family.  His previous owner had two young kids so Milo is good with kids.  Occasionally, when he's excited Milo can be a little mouthy so his new owner will need to continue correcting this behavior.   Milo's best home would have a fenced yard, no more apartment life for this sweet boy.  Another canine brother/sister of the same size would be wonderful for him but not required. Milo doesn't realize his own size and would probably play to rough with smaller dogs. His previous family had a stay-at-home mom so we would like his furever home to have someone home most of the time.  If you are looking for an active buddy and sweet boy to spoil, Milo might just be your guy. 

Milo was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. He will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on February 15th ready for adoption! To apply to adopt Milo, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 
**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**

IMPORTANT: For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a strictly-enforced signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

All dogs listed as on HOLD are NOT available for viewing by the public, unless you are their owner. 
Once a dog is no longer on HOLD, it is able to be viewed by the public, participate in meet & greets, and be adopted!

Adoption cost per dog is $99.00 (puppies under 6 months of age are $150.00). The adoption fee includes the following: OH license good for this calendar year, DA2PP, Bordetella vaccine, Heartworm testing, dewormer, and spay/neuter.  Flea treatment will be provided if fleas are noticed.  All dogs will be spayed/neutered and microchipped before leaving the facility.  An e-collar may be purchased for $15.00.  Because most of our dogs were picked up as strays, we have no knowledge of any behavior or health issues.  Stray dogs are held for 72 hours so that the owners have a chance to redeem them. After that time they are vetted and placed up for adoption. We welcome and encourage the cross posting of our dog's pictures to increase adoptions.

Iris. 3 Years Old. Spayed Female. Hound Mix. Brown/Black. 53 lbs.
I am such a busy bee.  I just can’t seem to settle down, well if you have a treat I will sit long enough to take it then I am off and on the go!  My colors are beautiful and I love to snuggle.  A nice scratch around the ears or a belly rub is always appreciated.  I have a lot of energy so it will be important that my new family takes me for long walks, hiking or maybe even running.  The more exercise I get the better behaved I will be in the home.  Tire me out!  My manners are still a work in progress.  I do know sit, give paw and lay down but I have a lot more to learn.  If you have never owned a hound please do a little research on my breed.  I don’t bark often but when I do you will know it. My nose is constantly to the ground trying to find out what has been around.  I love all sorts of toys so stock up before you take me home.  I arrived on December 24 because there were too many animals in the home. I did have a litter of puppies and was a great mom bringing them up. If you think I will be a nice fit to your home please call to schedule a time to meet with me.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Cane! I'm estimated to be a Boxer mix born around 3/18/2014. I weight around 50 pounds. I was surrendered to the shelter in Texas because I kept getting out of the yard.  I have lived with other dogs and love to play ball and go for walks.  I ride well in the car but want to ride shotgun.  I fence does keep me where I should be but I'll run off if loose so make sure to keep me contained.  Obedience classes for adult dogs and puppies can be incredibly helpful for both animals and humans. It helps you understand what makes me tick and will give me a better idea of what you want me to do. It’s a win/win and it will also strengthen the bond between us! Apply for me today!

My adoption fee is $60.00. Adoption applications can be filled out at CCHS or online through our website, www.cchs-petshelter.org. Applications are not first come, first served. All applications will be reviewed by the adoption committee and the home chosen will be the one considered to be the best match. All dogs and puppies have been vaccinated for Distemper and Bordetella, dewormed and microchipped. If old enough, they will be vaccinated for Rabies and blood tested for Heartworm, Lymes, Anaplasmosis and Erlichiosis. Dogs and puppies will be spayed or neutered before adoption.

CCHS is proud to be a No-Kill Humane Society. As a private, non-profit charity, our work depends on donations and volunteers to keep going. We are committed to helping the animals that enter our doors and finding each the best possible forever home. CCHS has been inspected and licensed by the Department of Animal Health - DATCP. Our license is #268235-DS

animal.description:
This very handsome boy is Casper, new to rescue. Casper is a very sweet boy who gets along well with other dogs does well indoors and loves playing out in the yard with his dog pals. He plays great with large and medium size dogs, but we're not sure he has been around small dogs and he seemed way too playful and a bit rough around the cat he met, so a cat-free home would be best. He is a young boy, about 75-80 pounds and needs to gain some much needed weight. When he first arrived to the shelter he was shaved down as his coat was so rough, but it is growing in beautifully now. The shelter adopted him out and he was left alone outdoors with inadequate fencing, so he would go wandering around the neighborhood and ended up back at animal control again. The owners decided to surrender him so we are happy to have him in rescue so he can be adopted to a family that knows the breed and has a fenced yard. According to the kind family who found him, he loved belly rubs and snuggling on the floor with people, did well with their dogs, he learned to use the doggie door and did not try to escape their fencing. Sadly, he was not well cared for in his first home and came in very thin, but he had no food guarding issues at all and ate well with all of the other dogs. Casper was very frightened when he was brought back to the shelter so he may be fearful in new situations. He is a sweet boy who deserves a great family who will care for him and give him the great home he deserves!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
NGPR dogs are in foster homes throughout the U.S., NOT Beacon, NY. View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed.

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.
animal.name: Casper - Sweet, Playful Boy!

animal.description:
Brisket is a dapper gentleman looking for a calm, cool, and collected household. As you can probably tell from his pictures - Brisket is visually impaired. A home with minimal stairs and children ages 12 and older would best suit this lovable fellas needs. Brisket has gotten along very well in his foster home and has never had any potty accidents. He has not been kenneled in his foster home, because he does not like the kennel and he is such a good boy and so well behaved he doesnt have to be. Brisket is a joy to take on walks, he has amazing leash manners and follows very well. He learned very quickly where his bed was, and his water and food bowls in the household. Brisket uses his nose and front paws to guide himself. He will need a bit of guidance by his human at first to become oriented with new surroundings. Brisket is a very quiet guy, only barks when hes chasing squirrels while dreaming. He has been in foster care with 2 dogs smaller than him and has been great. It would be best that Brisket is in a home with no dogs his size or larger, as they make him nervous and uneasy. This gentle and loving guy is ready for his forever home. 

Brisket was found as a stray dog wandering in the country in Southeast Missouri when he was taken in by Brave Animal Rescue. Routine bloodwork that was needed for him to be neutered showed unusual liver levels. An X-ray was done and we were shocked to find a bullet ludged in his liver. At this point, he is on a special liver food but the vet does not see a need for a risky surgery to remove the bullet. Brisket has also undergone lifesaving heartworm treatment. Lets find this total gem of a guy the best home ever, he deserves it!

We believe Brisket is around 5 years old and is a lab mix. He is fostered in a private home in Lincoln. The adoption fee is $350 which covers vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter(when old enough). The adoption fee helps cover the cost of these vetting procedures. Unless the bio is marked adoption pending, s/he is still available for adoption. If youre interested in adopting this puppy, please submit an inquiry or email BraveAnimalRescue@gmail.com to ask about our adoption process (please check your spam or junk email if you do not hear back from us within a few business days). We are 100% volunteer staffed and will respond to your email as soon as possible. After you have submitted an application and been approved, we will set up a meet and greet between you and the puppy. Preference is given to applicants with a verifiable vetting history, fenced yard, and homeownership. Please be sure to follow us on Facebook and Instagram to learn more about Brave Animal Rescue and our mission.

animal.description:
IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET, PLEASE COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION FOUND ON OUR WEBSITE HTTP://FUREVERTAILS.COM/ADOPTIONS. We process applications ONLY - there is no guarantee that you will get a response to an inquiry.

MEET PRADA:

Prada entered the shelter as a stray that was never reclaimed. She is estimated to be around 5 years old and weighs 68lbs. Prada is a super sweet girl, in fact she is quite a marshmellow! She is gentle with taking treats, has manageable energy and is always happy to meet new faces! Prada walks well on a leash and is crate trained, though she would prefer to be with people. She is not a chewer or destructive at all. She doesn't jump up on people and when she is really excited her little nub of a tail wags non-stop! Prada is good with other dogs but has not yet been introduced to cats. We would recommend a home with older children due to her size. 

Unfortunately, Prada has tested heartworm positive and will need to complete treatement before her adoption is finalized. Prada is seeking family that's ultimate goal is adoption while she undergoes heartworm treatment that is covered financially by the rescue; the treatment will take place over the next 5 months. Anyone interested in a foster-to-adopt opportunity will be required to follow the well defined treatment plan and transport Prada to her vet appointments that will include a spay surgery late February in Clinton Twp, and 3 heartworm injection appointments in April and May (also in Clinton Twp). She will require that she is kept quiet while she undergoes heartworm treatment, which shouldn't be difficult with her gentle nature. Dogs treated for heartworm typically enjoy happy, healthy long lives - the only future requirement is that they remain on heartworm prevention year round. Prada is a great dog that will make an amazing addition to some lucky family looking to love her furever!

Furever Tails Animal Rescue covers all the costs for the mdeical care associated with the heartworm treatment. Fosters are required to follow the protocol provided by our veterinarian and approved by the American Heartworm Society. 

Prada is:
Current on Rabies and Distemper
Dewormed
Heartworm Tested: Positive and is currently undergoing treatment
Receiving Heartworm and Flea Prevention
Microchipped
Scheduled to be spayed in February
Will be treated for any medical concerns prior to finalizing adoption.

ADOPTION FEE: $275

FUREVER TAILS IS A NON-PROFIT, NO-KILL, FOSTER HOME BASED ANIMAL RESCUE BASED OUT OF OAKLAND TOWNSHIP, MI. OUR FOSTER ANIMALS ARE LIVING IN FOSTER HOMES AND TREATED LIKE FAMILY UNTIL THEY FIND THEIR OWN FUREVER FAMILIES. OUR ADOPTION PROECESS REQUIRES AN APPLICATION TO BE COMPLETED AND APPROVED BEFORE A MEET-N-GREET WITH THE ANIMAL CAN TAKE PLACE. ADOPTION FEES ARE NECESSARY TO HELP US COVER VETTING COSTS FOR OUR RESCUED ANIMALS. UNFORTUNATELY AT THIS TIME WE ARE NOT CURRENTLY ADOPTING OUT OF THE STATE OF MI.

animal.description:
Sallie Mae is a two (2) year old, 40 pound lab mix that came to us with her litter of five puppies that were born under the porch of a home in south GA. The homeowner had been feeding several strays and reached out to us to help the little family and get them out of the cold. We took her and four other dogs on the property, including another pregnant one that just had eight puppies.

Sallie did an amazing job of caring for her puppies but it took a toll on her and she was very malnourished and a little worse for the wear when we got her. A wonderful foster family welcomed Sallie Mae and her family and took wonderful care of them. The puppies all have applications and now it's Sallie Maes turn. 

She is wonderful with people and fine with young kids. She is a little shy still, so we want to make sure she is in a secure home and one where she will get a lot of love, direction and guidance. If you would like to foster to adopt Sallie Mae, please go to www.atlantalabrescue.com to fill out an application.

If you love decadent, delicious, and delightful desserts, then MatchDog has your dish! Welcome the Cutie Pie Pups - chock full of fluffy morsels to tempt your sweet tooth! Indulge today!

Are you looking for a dog with a unique look? Let us introduce you to a handsome, multi-colored pup with just the right amount of sweetness. Meet Jaffa! A 1-2-year-old male Australian Shepherd WEIGHING 30-35 POUNDS, this pup is quite special. Jaffa is playful, completely housetrained, and great with kids. He also gets along well with other dogs, easily making new friends. Australian Shepherds are known for being intelligent and hard working, affectionate and good-natured. Jaffa looks to check all of those boxes. A fabulous find, he won't be around long. If you're looking for that special, one-of-a-kind companion, don't delay! Apply for Jaffa today!

If you think you are a perfect match for Jaffa please complete an application fully: https://www.petstablished.com/organization/243592 

Jaffa has been fully vetted, is up to date on all vaccinations and on preventatives for heartworm, flea, and tick. We cannot guarantee breed information. You will find price guidelines for adoption at matchdogrescue.org and you can read about the whole adoption process and what MatchDog Rescue provides with each dog.

This gorgeous MatchDog is currently being fostered and cared for at our own facility so as to look and feel his best when he meets you on Saturday, February 13, 2021. For the very best chance of securing a meet with this dog, you must be available all day on this date. 

If you see a pending notification on this dog, it means we have informed the lucky family selected as the best match for this particular dog and they have agreed to come to the transport/event with the goal of taking the dog to their forever home. If for any reason this plan falls through, we will change the picture back to its original format and revisit other applications.

animal.description:
COURTESY POSTING LOLA IS NOT AT WCGHS
Do not click on "Ask about LOLA" Thank you!
FOR INFORMATION, CONTACT OWNER DIRECTLY AT:
11kayla11@gmail.com

Lola is a 5-year-old lab mix with black and white coloring. I rescued Lola from a shelter about a week ago when I was told that she was going to be put down if she was not picked up. Lola has been nothing but sweet towards my family, including my 4-year old son and developmentally disabled brother (who tends to be rough at times). She has greeted everyone with licks and always wants to be pet. However, as a mother, business owner, and nurse, I do not have the time necessary to provide Lola with the life that she deserves. 



Lola would love to be placed with someone who spends most of their time at home. I could see her being very helpful to someone with anxiety or depression or who wants to be comforted at times, as she constantly likes to give her human(s) affection and show them that she is there. She is very easy-going and is content lounging around the house but also likes to go for walks and run around in the grass. 



Lola has not had any accidents in the house and she has not chewed anything up. However, trash cans need to be put up (especially when no one is home) because Lola gets curious about food scraps! Lola is about 100 pounds and loves to cuddle. She does well with kids, likes to “shake” your hand, and loves being outside! 



Lola’s complete background is unknown. She is usually very quiet and doesn’t bark but when approached by men that she doesn’t know, she barks and sometimes growls. Her paperwork from the previous shelter that she was rescued from states that she bit a person or another animal, but no further details were given by the previous owner or shelter. However, the previous owner also lied about this dog, saying that she was already put down, so the reliability of the biting claim is unknown. Lola has been sweet to everyone she has spent time with so far and even lets my 4-year old climb all over her. The employee at the previous shelter also shared that they did not see any signs of aggression with Lola. 



If you are interested in meeting this sweet girl and adding her to your family, please reach out to Kayla via email at 11kayla11@gmail.com with your name, location, and why you think Lola could be a good fit for you or your family! From there, I would love to set up a time for her to meet you (and any of your pets).

This sweet little lady is Hadley! ?

Hadley is a two year old Boxer. She came to us after being dumped with her puppy in Houston. The person that found them kept her puppy, but Hadley had no plan. Unfortunately, Hadley was heartworm positive and had to go through treatment before traveling to Wisconsin to search for her forever home.

Hadley is your typical Boxer. She is full of wiggles, has no concept of personal space, and thinks she is a lap dog. ? She is a petite girl, weighing in at around 40 pounds. She enjoys going for walks, and does great on leash. Hadley can co exist with other dogs, but would do best in a home as an only dog. She has been tested with children and would do best with older children. The fast movements and loud noises of young children make her a bit nervous. We don’t know much about her story before she came to us, but our guess is she lived outside. She is working on crate and potty training. She has been doing great in her foster home and we are so excited for her to find her forever home. She will make a perfect companion

animal.description:
TONYA: Will be 12 weeks old on 1/28/20, 4lbs, Sharpie/Beagle Mix, Spayed Female, Estimated to Be About 35 to 40lbs Full Grown 

 As we head into 2021 let's SHARPIE or SLAY? We're not sure it's going to catch on. But we are sure that these guys are stupidly cute! Please welcome our latest crew of wrinkly perfection. These guys are currently hanging in thier foster homes eating, sleeping, playing and growing. These guys were dumped at a shelter in TN at 6 weeks old. And are now nice and cozy in their NYC foster homes getting ready for thier big day (adoption day). These guys are going to be about 35 to 40lbs full grown. Their adopters need to be ready to take on puppy training and potty training. They will do well in an active home. They would be okay with respectful children 10 years and up and parents who are willing to navigate teething puppies and children :) These guys will need at least 90 minutes of outdoor time a day as adults. Interested in adopting please go to www.socialteesnyc.org or reach out to your point person if you are already approved. 
 

Her Foster Says: Tonyas blue eyes were the first thing I noticed about her. Then her cute little wrinkles around her nose. She enjoys spending her day napping and taking play breaks where she likes to chase her human or a dog friend around the room. She has a calm demeanor, especially for a puppy, and enjoys sitting on your lap and cuddling. Tonya learns fast and has almost mastered pee pads. Whoever adopts her is in for a real treat. She was the only girl in her litter and is a chunkster bigger than her brothers. I love her white socks and how she hops around like a rabbit when she plays lol. Oh and she looks like a baby pig with her pink belly up. 

What is a Beagle?: A beagle is in fact a type of hound and super scent oriented. They have a great sense of smell and superior tracking instincts. Fun fact, beagles are the primary breed used as detection dogs for prohibited agriculture. The breed's most famous representative is the world's very beloved cartoon character Snoopy! Beagles are very popular family dogs because they are known to be sweet and easy to train. (On a sad note, they are commonly used in testing labs because they are so trusting and docile, and there are many rescues specifically dedicated to saving beagles from the chemical testing world.) 

What does owning this dog entail?: Plenty of socialization, exercise, and mental stimulation is key for keeping this medium active pup happy. Generally you can expect to need to give this canine a minimum of 90 minutes of outdoor time every day. A perfect walking, hiking, and adventure buddy. We strongly recommend a basic training course to get a more solid feel for this pup's individual needs and how to best communicate with each other. Beagles often have some prey drive though, so adults can be quick to go for small animals like squirrels and may not be great choices for homes with small animals. They can be very stop and go walking buddies sometimes because of that crazy nose of theirs, so strolls take a while sometimes. They are also quick to take off if they catch a scent, so you have to be extra careful with beagles off leash because they will disappear if you haven't done enough recall training with them -- or even if you have sometimes, their instincts just take over. We strongly recommend not having them off leash in an unenclosed area.

PLEASE NOTE: This animal is not at the Social Tees office all of our dogs and cats are in foster homes while they wait to find their forever families. :) If youd like to apply to adopt this pet, please complete an adoption application at socialteesnyc.org. Because we are a small team and receive hundreds of applications each week, we are unable to respond to every application and every inquiry email, but we do our best. Please have patience! If your application is approved, you will for sure hear from us. If you have questions, please take a look at the Adoption and Fostering FAQs etc. on our website as all common questions are answered there. Thank you for your understanding and flexibility as we work to save these innocent lives!! 

LEARN MORE ABOUT US: socialteesnyc.org; Instagram via @socialteesnyc; Facebook.com/socialteesanimalrescue

****Please do not message the rescue asking if this dog is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Yogi
*Age: 1 year
*Current Weight: 70
*Rescued from: Texas
*Adoption fee: $375 
*Health: up to date on required vaccines

Just look at that sweet face and you know this boy is full of personality.  Yogi is a fun loving dog but has to be re-homed, the apartment life is not for him.  So, apartment homes will not be considered for him.  This playful boy needs exercise so a fenced yard is needed for him.  (Acreage with an invisible fence may be considered.)   Yogi is great with other dogs so he would love a canine sister or brother.  Yogi is house trained and loves his toys.  If you have the perfect home for this fun loving, happy, playful boy, Yogi says he can't wait to meet you!  

Yogi was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. He will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on February 15th ready for adoption! To apply to adopt Yogi, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 
**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**

IMPORTANT:  For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a strictly-enforced signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
Aki is a beautiful purebred female German Shepherd, almost 2 years old. She was rescued at the end of November weighing only 37 pounds. She is now at a healthier weight, approximately 43 pounds, and will be a medium sized dog. Vet confirmed ideal weight to be approximately 50 lbs.

She has a sweet, playful personality, but is also anxious, fearful and prefers a female owner. Aki can be skittish around men initially, but is learning to trust. She is mostly house and crate trained, with the occasional accident.

She is UTD on shots, not spayed as we were waiting for her to be healthy and strong enough for it. She needs to be in a home without small children; a fenced yard is required. She may do well with male dogs; we are not sure how she is with cats. She is learning to walk on a leash.

Aki is going to need someone who is calm and patient with her. She came from a bad situation.

If you're interested in adopting Aki, please fill out an application at aylasacres.org.

There is an adoption fee and a home visit is required.

animal.description:
0121033

Sweet Mira. This sweet young lady is looking for a safe, nurturing home. She can be a little shy meeting people and trying new things. However, when she warms to you she will be your shadow! She loves playing with her foster siblings and is gentle with her feline siblings too. We think she is mixed with Boxer as well as the Black Mouth Cur. 

At 40 pounds she is the perfect size for someone who wants a smaller dog that acts like a big dog. In photos she appears bigger but on the shorter side. 

She has been learning how to walk on leash and is quickly catching on. She would do best with another dog or active kids, so that she is mentally and physically stimulated. Exercise is a must. 

Although she is mostly potty-trained (about 80%), she can be hesitant to go outside alone. You will have to be patient while she builds up her confidence with being outside on her own. She needs another dog in the home--another dog will help her learn the ropes. She is crate-trained and will even go into her crate on her own when she needs a break from her foster siblings. 

She has quickly become one of our favorite fosters and we are so excited for her to get the loving stable home she deserves.

Carly needs a home with:
- no children under the age of 12

Meet Carly! Carly is a peppy 10 month old Shepherd/Hound mix ready to take on all of life's new adventures! She's an energetic girl with the zoomies to match and she would love a dedicated adopter who can help her get her energy out. She is a playful pup who loves to chase after toys and would love a yard to run around in or plenty of hiking adventures to take off on so she can sniff as much as her heart desires. Carly is a total smarty pants too - she already knows 'sit' and 'down' and can't wait to add more tricks to her resume. She loves treats and will make a great training buddy for anyone ready to work with her. She can be a little nervous at times and is looking to build her confidence with a patient, forever family to show her how fun and care-free life can be for her. Carly needs a home with no children under the age of 12 because she's still working on her manners and can be mouthy and uncomfortable with some handling. She's a sweet girl who's ready to settle into someone's lap for all the kisses and attention they can spare. If Carly sounds like the perfect match for you, adopt her today!

If you're interested in adopting Carly, please email a completed adoption application to adoptions@kitsap-humane.org. Adoption applications and more information about our adoption process can be found on our website here: https://www.kitsap-humane.org/adopt/how-to-adopt/. Once your application has been received, you will be placed in line to have your application reviewed. All applicants are pre-screened over the phone, and then are scheduled for a time to come in and meet the dog at the shelter. Roman was brought to the shelter as a stray, and sadly no one came looking for him.  So now Roman is looking for his forever home.  Little Roman is about 40lbs, and about 1 year old.  He is still very much a puppy!  He has lots of energy, and very few manners.  He is great raw material looking for someone to love and teach him how to be a proper gentleman.  We have not yet assessed Roman with other dogs, but our initial observations are he may be best as an only pet.  We will update his profile when we know if he is dog friendly.  We think he is a bit much for little kids, so we recommend children over 10 years old.  We do not cat test.  

FOLLOW THESE INSTRUCTIONS TO BE CONSIDERED: 

To adopt, complete the application at tarnj.org/adopt

If you have any questions at all, please DO NOT use the PetFinder inquiry form as we do not respond to those. Questions should be sent to info@tarnj.org. 

An application is required before any meets are scheduled so the best way to be considered is to apply ASAP at tarnj.org/adopt.

We are all volunteer-run and do our best to respond to every application. If there is a match with your application, you should hear from us within 2-5 days. If you do not hear from us, please check your Junk folder or email us for an update.

APPLY AT FODRescue.org

Emma was found alone outside. She is a sweetheart who loves people and gets along with smaller dogs. She has started crate and house training. At about 5 years old, she has a lot of life and love ahead of her.

All of our rescues are in a foster home where they receive one on one care, attention, and training. 

We welcome out of state adopters but there is an additional fee of $20 for a veterinary health certificate. We do not ship our animals- they all need to be picked up in northeast Missouri.

Please fill out an adoption application at our website: FODRescue.org, or call (660) 342-6023 and leave a message. Thank you!!

animal.description:
Meet Parker!

Parker is a super sweet pup with plenty of love to give.
He is being adopted out as a hospice pet due to a significant life threatening heart condition. He needs to be kept calm with no aerobic exercise or increased stress. 
Parker is a very high energy dog, so this would be a commitment his new owners will need to make.
He is a smart and curious dog and enjoys going on short leash walks. 
He is also a huge fan of toys!
Parker has interacted with other dogs during his time at the shelter and he is playful. However, to his rough play style conflicting with the type of lifestyle he needs to live - another dog in the home may not be a healthy idea. 
Additionally, he does get easily over-aroused and can be very jumpy - so we encourage a home without young/small children at this time.


He was previously in a foster home and this is what his foster Mom said about him:
Parker loves to play! He is a bit high energy, is always up for a good tummy rub, and also enjoys walking the neighborhood and exploring. Not sure if he would be suited for homes with kids since he is strong and can play a little rough or easily knock them over. He seems to be house trained. Loves snacks and dog toys.

If you think Parker might be a good fit, come meet him at Charleston Animal Society!
